The EstNLTK package bundles the Vabamorf morphological analyzer
(https://github.com/Filosoft/vabamorf), which is dual-licensed under
the LGPL-2.1 and a separate commercial license. Users distributing
this server must comply with Vabamorf's license terms in addition to
this project's Apache-2.0 license.

POS tag inventory and morphological categories are produced by Vabamorf
and follow the conventions documented in EstNLTK.

This product also bundles compressed Estonian fastText word embeddings
(file: /opt/models/fasttext-et-mini in the Docker image) used by the
find_related_words tool. The vectors are licensed under
Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 (CC-BY-SA-3.0):

  Original vectors:
    Grave, E., Bojanowski, P., Gupta, P., Joulin, A., Mikolov, T.
    "Learning Word Vectors for 157 Languages." LREC 2018.
    https://fasttext.cc/docs/en/crawl-vectors.html

  Compression and quantization:
    Bernhard Liebl, "fasttext-et-mini" (2021).
    Zenodo: https://zenodo.org/records/4905385

The bundled model file remains under CC-BY-SA-3.0 — anyone
redistributing this Docker image or any derivative model file must
preserve attribution and apply share-alike to derivative model files.
The rest of estonian-mcp (source code, server.py, etc.) stays under
Apache-2.0; the share-alike obligation applies only to the embeddings
file itself.
